<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,482,723]" box="[189,751,482,508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Hardwicke’s entry for this species is as follows:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,482,723]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
“ 
<taxonomicName authority="Antidysentricum Rox." authorityName="Antidysentricum Rox." box="[202,555,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Echites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,489,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Echites Antidysentricum</emphasis>
Rox.
</taxonomicName>
— A small tree in the forests about Hurdwar. Leaves opposite, half or subpetioled, ovate, oblong, pointed, entire, waved, smooth, shining, one nerved, with many pairs of lateral, parallel, ribs. The Linnean characters of the fructification, do not strictly agree with this plant. The nectary is here wanting. Anthers almost at the bottom of the tube, filaments, scarcely any. The follicles agree with those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Antidysentricum. The" authorityName="Antidysentricum. The" box="[528,878,660,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[528,816,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nerium Antidysentricum</emphasis>
. The
</taxonomicName>
seeds are in great repute among the natives of Hindustan as a vermifuge.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,762,1003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Hardwicke provided a reasonable description that clearly applies to the plant now known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Wall. ex G. Don. However" authorityName="Wall. ex G. Don. However" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Buch. - Ham." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Holarrhena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Holarrhena pubescens</emphasis>
Wall. ex G.Don. However
</taxonomicName>
, he also cited 
<taxonomicName box="[784,1080,798,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antidysentericum">
<emphasis box="[784,1080,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nerium antidysentericum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. as a synonym. Linnaeus confounded two taxa in describing this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Panigrahi G." box="[743,924,833,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="464 - 467" refId="ref9937" refString="Panigrahi G. 1987. Echites antidysenterica (L.) Roxb. ex Fleming and Holarrhena antidysenterica (L.) Wall., validly published synonyms of Wallida antidysenterica. Taxon 36: 464 - 467. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1221451" type="journal article" year="1987">Panigrahi 1987</bibRefCitation>
) – the 
<collectingRegion box="[1002,1036,833,859]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lankan endemic, now referred to as 
<taxonomicName box="[263,559,869,895]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Wrightia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antidysenterica">
<emphasis box="[263,559,869,895]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Wrightia antidysenterica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) R.Br., and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wall. ex G. Don. However" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Buch. - Ham." box="[768,1041,869,895]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Holarrhena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[768,1041,869,895]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Holarrhena pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is widespread across East Africa and Asia (De 
<bibRefCitation author="Kruif A. P. M. de" box="[508,645,905,931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref9630" refString="Kruif A. P. M. de 1981. A revision of Holarrhena R. Br. (Apocynaceae). Mededelingen Landbouwhogeschool Wageningen 81 - 2: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1981">Kruif 1981</bibRefCitation>
). As Hardwicke did not explicitly exclude Linnaeus’s 
<typeStatus box="[1312,1363,905,931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
or name from his 
<taxonomicName box="[372,660,940,966]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Echites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antidysentericus">
<emphasis box="[372,660,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Echites antidysentericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has to be considered a new combination based on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Nerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antidysentericum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nerium antidysentericum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This represents an earlier publication of the combination than that by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fleming J." box="[1209,1395,976,1002]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="153 - 196" refId="ref9233" refString="Fleming J. 1810. A catalogue of Indian medicinal plants and drugs, with their names in the Hindustani and Sanscrit languages. Asiatick Researches 11: 153 - 196." type="journal article" year="1810">Fleming (1810)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
